g.text: This is our main source of truth, all other tables can be replayed from
- for now only mainnet events are indexed,
but nothing would need to change to support testnets
as all tables use a composite key with the chainId
- it's populated/updated each time an proposal event is added to|
the events table (ProposalVoted | ProposalVotedV2 | ProposalVoteRevoked | ProposalVoteRevokedV2)
- this table is a aggregation of blockchain + github metadata
based on the events from the events table and the
- it's populated/updated each time an proposal event is added to|
the events table (ProposalExecuted | ProposalApproved | ProposalExpired | ProposalDequeued | ProposalQueued)
- chainId INTEGER // foreignKey to chains table
- id BIGINT // proposal Id on chain
- pastId BIGINT // past iteration of a proposal (inferred by the cgp)
- cgp BIGINT // governance proposal id in github
- url TEXT // forum url for discussion
- cgpUrl TEXT // github url for hotlinking
- cgpUrlRaw TEXT // github url for downloading the .md file
- title TEXT // title to display from github
- author TEXT // github user that authored the file
- timestamp INTEGER // time of the ProposalQueued event
- executedAt INTEGER // time of the ProposalExecuted event
- proposer TEXT // address (0x123) that submitted the proposal
- transactionCount INTEGER // transaction count on the proposal on chain
- networkWeight NUMERIC // networkWeight of the proposal, updated each time a vote is received
